Just an Intro before Linux commands.

"Unix" is the grand father of all the modern Operating Systems.

There are basically two Types of Operating Systems.
1) Microsoft Windows
2) Unix - MAC OS X, Linux, Android, Chrome OS, PS4 OS.

Linux based OS means Linux Distributions.
They are:
1) Debian GNU
2) Ubuntu Linux
3) Fedora
4) Raspberry Pi OS
5) Slackware
6) Red Hat Enterprise Linux

Linux kernel is a part of OS which interacts between hardware and software.


Terminal ---> Shell --->  OS

Terminal is a program that runs shell.
In Early days terminal is a physical device, now it is upgraded to software terminal.

Shell takes commands from terminal and gives them to OS to perform.





